nodeDataArray.text_title: 60. My headset is not connected to my computer

CHECK_QUESTION.119: Are you saying that your headset is not connected to your computer?

ANSWER_TEXT.120:
Connect a Wired USB Headset.

Introduction:

This page describes how to connect your wired USB headset .

Details:

Connect your headset's USB plug to your computer; your computer should automatically install the correct drivers.

You can check to see if your device has been recognized by clicking on (right side, near the top) Options > Audio Device and clicking on the dropdown under Select the device you want to use for audio calls Your device should appear on that dropdown menu if it is enabled.
NOTE : If your device does not appear then escalate the ticket to Client/Field Support.

To see if your device is working properly click on (in the bottom left corner of the Main Lync window) Select Primary Device > Check Call Quality .

Follow the audio instructions.

If you do not hear any audio instructions, or if you do not hear a playback of your recording click on (right side, near the top) Options > Audio Device and select your device in the dropdown under Select the device you want to use for audio calls.
